[Script Info]
; WP-H3 repro: kobayashi ep7 t=268 ornate sign "It's because I wanna curse her
; to death" -- GPU-raster vs CPU divergence (was ~115/255 on the live frame).
; Verbatim override tags + real pSigns style from the embedded English track,
; made static so a single screenshot reproduces it. Needs Convalescence.ttf on
; the fontconfig path (extract from the kobayashi mkv attachments); with a
; substitute sans font the thin ornate strokes -- hence the effect -- change.
;
; ROOT CAUSE (fixed in libass): layer {=31} draws ONLY its drop shadow
; (\alpha&HFE&\4a&H00&) with a sub-quantum \shad0.1 under \blur. The CPU sets
; FILTER_NONZERO_SHADOW from the un-quantized offset and renders a zero-offset
; shadow; the deferred emitter gated the shadow RUN on the blur-QUANTIZED offset
; (rounded to 0) and dropped it, so the GPU path was missing the whole shadow
; layer. Fix: gate render_shadow_deferred on FILTER_NONZERO_SHADOW.
;   {=31} shadow raster-vs-CPU: 229/255 -> 0.5/255 (black bg);  live t=268: 115 -> 0.7.
; Residual (SEPARATE, pre-existing): {=30}'s \blur20 parchment is the large-sigma
; gaussian-approx gap (~3.4/255 gray, ~0.7 on the live video) beyond the M5-
; certified sigma range; unaffected by the shadow fix.
